        <title>Vi set color scheme , line numbers and syntax highlighting</title>
        <link>https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 23 Apr 2013 16:34:21 +0300</pubDate>
        
        <guid>https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/</guid>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;Today I wanted to to set the Color Scheme in vi / vim in my Linux. The default configuration looks ugly:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_default.png&#34;
	width=&#34;654&#34;
	height=&#34;464&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_default_hu_2a5d51681eb9b971.png 480w, https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_default_hu_b2cd39647ef4cf42.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Default coloscheme for linux vi editor&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;140&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;338px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I wanted to look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_evening.png&#34;
	width=&#34;654&#34;
	height=&#34;464&#34;
	srcset=&#34;https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_evening_hu_b8b4610a80cbb50c.png 480w, https://manios.org/2013/04/23/vi-set-color-scheme-line-numbers-and-syntax-highlighting/vi_colorscheme_evening_hu_569a2e3590458f.png 1024w&#34;
	loading=&#34;lazy&#34;
	
		alt=&#34;Evening colorcheme for linux vi editor&#34;
	
	
		class=&#34;gallery-image&#34; 
		data-flex-grow=&#34;140&#34;
		data-flex-basis=&#34;338px&#34;
	
&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So after some searching in the web I found an article in &lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;http://talkbinary.com/linux/how-to-set-the-color-scheme-in-vim/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;talkbinary&lt;/a&gt; and I did the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create in your home directory a file called .exrc
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;touch ~/.exrc
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Open this file and insert the following parameters:
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;set&lt;/span&gt; number
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;syntax on
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;colorscheme evening
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Save the file and you are done! Now you have a nice colourfull VI editor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</description>
